  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "反者道之動，"
    },
    {
      "text": "弱者道之用。"
    },
    {
      "text": "天下萬物生於有，有生於無。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "高以下為基，貴以賤為本，有以無為用，此其反也。動皆知其所無，則物通矣。故曰「反者道之動」也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "柔弱同通，不可窮極。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天下之物皆以有為生，有之所始，以無為本，將欲全有，必反於無也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
